The package you are installing is part of Rudix.

Rudix is a collection of pre-built Unix-like software delivered as packages for Macintoshes.
This package is self-contained and has everything it needs to work.

The binaries, libraries and documentation will be installed in /usr/local/
Python modules will be installed in /Library/Python/*/site-packages/

You will now be guided through the steps necessary to install this software.

Thank you for choosing Rudix! For more information, visit rudix.org.